# GAPOSA Automated Paperwork System

The frontend foundation for the **Gateway ICT Polytechnic Saapade (GAPOSA)** Automated Paperwork System is now complete! The interface has been designed with a premium, modern aesthetic using standard HTML, CSS, and vanilla JS, as requested, to allow maximum flexibility for your future backend integrations.

## What Was Completed

### 1. Project Foundation & Premium Styling
- **Location:** The project is located in your desktop at `\web design\school_paperwork_system\`.
- **Styling ([style.css](file:///c:/Users/DELL/Desktop/web%20design/school_paperwork_system/style.css)):**
  - Designed a high-end glassmorphic aesthetic using pure, external CSS.
  - Implemented dynamic, animated background elements ("blobs") and modern gradients.
  - Implemented a consistent design system (colors, spacing, and typography using Google 'Inter' font).
  - Designed both a primary theme (Deep Blue/Gold) for students, and an alternate theme (Teal/Amber) for the administrative panel.

### 2. Dual-Role Authentication Interfaces
- **Student Login ([index.html](file:///c:/Users/DELL/Desktop/web%20design/school_paperwork_system/index.html)):** Clean and intuitive prompt for Student Name and Matric Number.
- **Admin Login ([admin.html](file:///c:/Users/DELL/Desktop/web%20design/school_paperwork_system/admin.html)):** Themed with admin colors, prompting for Staff ID and Password.
- Both forms are temporarily wired to use `localStorage` to navigate directly to their respective dashboards.

### 3. Student Dashboard Experience ([dashboard.html](file:///c:/Users/DELL/Desktop/web%20design/school_paperwork_system/dashboard.html) & [app.js](file:///c:/Users/DELL/Desktop/web%20design/school_paperwork_system/app.js))
- **Chat-Based UI:** The main component mimics an AI-assisted messaging app for paperwork.
- **Operations:**
  - Mocked responses for "Memos" and "IT Letters".
  - Created a custom-styled File Attachment area designed specifically for "Yellow file submission" uploads.
  - Interactive "quick action" buttons for faster navigation.

### 4. Administrative Dashboard ([admin-dashboard.html](file:///c:/Users/DELL/Desktop/web%20design/school_paperwork_system/admin-dashboard.html) & [admin.js](file:///c:/Users/DELL/Desktop/web%20design/school_paperwork_system/admin.js))
- **Control Panel:** Allows school admins to easily oversee paperwork tracking.
- **Features:**
  - Key statistical highlights (e.g. Disbursed Letters, Pending Yellow Files).
  - Interface module to select a document type (Memo, Statement of Result, IT Letter), attach a file, and target a specific matriculation number.
  - Interactive loading state when a document "upload" is triggered.

## Verification & Usage

You can launch and verify the application directly from your file explorer.

### Testing the App
1. Open **[index.html](file:///c:/Users/DELL/Desktop/web%20design/school_paperwork_system/index.html)** in your browser ([c:\Users\DELL\Desktop\web design\school_paperwork_system\index.html](file:///Users/DELL/Desktop/web%20design/school_paperwork_system/index.html)).
2. **Student Test:** Enter a name and your Matric number, then hit *"Login"*.
   - Try the chat bot by clicking **"Get IT Letter"** or typing *"I need to submit my yellow file"*.
   - Notice the rich conversational bubbles and file mockup downloads.
3. **Admin Test:** Click the "Go to Admin Portal" link from the main login screen. Enter any mock ID/password.
   - You will land in the dark-teal administrator dashboard. Test the "Upload & Disburse Document" interactive button.

### 5. Secure Backend Architecture (Node.js & PostgreSQL)
We have laid the foundation for a highly secure Node.js (Express) backend located in the `/backend` directory.

- **[backend/server.js](file:///c:/Users/DELL/Desktop/web%20design/school_paperwork_system/backend/server.js)**: Contains the core logic with fundamental security layers:
  - **Helmet:** Automatically sets secure HTTP headers (like Frameguard to prevent clickjacking and Content Security Policies).
  - **CSURF:** Middleware instantiated to generate specific CSRF tokens that must be validated on every state-changing POST request.
- **[backend/routes/api.js](file:///c:/Users/DELL/Desktop/web%20design/school_paperwork_system/backend/routes/api.js)**: Houses the API endpoints. It utilizes `express-validator` to explicitly sanitize, trim, and escape all inputs before any processing occurs, preventing **Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)**.
- **[backend/db.js](file:///c:/Users/DELL/Desktop/web%20design/school_paperwork_system/backend/db.js)**: Controls the PostgreSQL connection pool. It uses strict parameterized queries (e.g., `SELECT * FROM table WHERE attr = $1`) to eliminate any chance of **SQL Injection**.

### Moving Forward
Because the UI is built strictly with external CSS and uncoupled JavaScript files ([app.js](file:///c:/Users/DELL/Desktop/web%20design/school_paperwork_system/app.js), [admin.js](file:///c:/Users/DELL/Desktop/web%20design/school_paperwork_system/admin.js)), you can easily swap out the mock validation logic for real API endpoint calls (to your new Node.js backend) whenever you are ready!

**Next Steps for You:**
1. Install [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/) and [PostgreSQL](https://www.postgresql.org/) on your computer.
2. Open a terminal in the `backend` folder and run `npm install express pg helmet csurf express-validator cors cookie-parser`
3. Update the database password inside [backend/db.js](file:///c:/Users/DELL/Desktop/web%20design/school_paperwork_system/backend/db.js) and start your server!
